x4freetext: HVEC MP Tandem accelerator of the
University and Technical University of Munich
source for negative polarized D- and
H- hydrogen ion beams. the value of the
polarization was 0.6.
The 50 mu-g/cm2 thick 123Sb isotopically enriched
(98.28%) target was evaporated onto an 8 mu-g/cm2
carbon backing.
The reaction products were momentum
separated by the Q3D magnetic spectrograph, at nine
angles between 6. and 52.5 degr., with both spin-up
and spin-down polarization in different magnetic
field settings in order to reach an excitation
energy of the residual nucleus of 4750 keV.
Outgoing alpha particles were identified by
the new proportional counter with cathode-strip readout
focal plane, designed to detect light ions such as p, d
for the Q3D with a position resolution of better than
0.1 mm, good particle identification and high count
rate.
The particles were stopped in a 7 mm thick
plastic scintillator (NE-104) which ensured both dE-E
particle identification and good position resolution.
All spectra were normalized with respect to the beam
current accumulated by a Faraday cup and analyzed
with the AUTOFIT shape fitting code
Statistical error
systematic error
